rComments: Course itself is easy, follows S/NS grading system, only has 2 midterms and a final. Lectures are confusing and poorly planned, prof will schedule half an hour for us to watch youtube videos individually, go through half the slides while stopping and repeating herself frequently, and have us finish the rest at home when they could be done in class

This prof is so sweet. She talks a lot and never manages to get through her powerpoint but she is so so nice and caring. Her grading criteria is so clear. Exams represent exactly what is in her powerpoints. I've taken three classes with her and she is the cutest, I loved her.

Prof. Cossette is probably my fav professor at uottawa so far. She's kind, caring, and clearly wants her students to do well. Her exams are fair and she gives out pre-tests which often have exam questions. Her ppts are content-heavy so additional notes aren't really needed. Would 100% take her again she deserves a higher rating!

Her teaching style is a little confusing because she switches between powerpoint. Exams are really straightforward and she gives pre tests which usually have questions which she includes in the exams.
Her exams are fair. She provide practice test before each exam which is really helpful. She really sweet and she made me thing of my HS profs. She a germ and deserve to have 5 star!!!

Very informative course! There are three exams and I would say her exams are fair. She will provide you with practice questions before each exam which was really helpful as well as she makes her expectations quite clear. As long as you attend lectures and study the PowerPoints, the exams won't be as challenging. Great professor overall!
Solid choice. Most of it is a review from BIO1140 or AP bio. She is very kind and the midterms are not difficult, although some questions are phrased oddly.

She seemed nice, but I only went to the online lecture for the first 2 weeks. She doesn't know how to work teams and her internet, camera, and audio were poor quality. Her lectures were mostly just her reading off slides. The midterms are pretty easy online because you have a lot of time to be able to search for answers.

Her lectures are very difficult to follow, she tends to jump around a lot through the slides and double back on herself. She isnt used to Teams or Zoom so if youre taking her course on line, prepare for some frustration. Testable material is always presented in the slides and they tend to be easy to follow. She seems very nice , just confusing

She is good with grades. She is not used to technology, confused (uses Teams). She is not organised - doesn't answer to emails, heavy PPT. But she really wants us to pass - gives key words, slides to study for the exam. Average for the 1st midterm : 89%, 2nd one : 83%. No other assignments.

Took this as an easy A, turns out its just a pass or fail and she never told us, my friend who took the class last semester told me! All the info is on the slides so I legit only went to class for the midterms and exam, got 85 in both midterms and barely studied. Its legit a mix of grade 12 bio and anatomy, super easy (for me at least).

Professor Cossette is a very sweet and kind lady. However, there is no teaching in her classroom. She cares about her students, but is extremely unorganized and cannot explain things AT ALL. The tests were always crammed and the expectations were unclear. The questions are also very vague and weirdly phrased. Avoid if you can.

I found her to be a good prof. She's very sweet! She does have a little bit of an accent but it wasn't hard to understand her. I 100% recommend going to class & taking notes on her slides while she's lecturing, that's all you'll need to study! The textbook is for in class assignments. She did cram a few chapters at the end since we ran out of time.

She is incredibly nice and sweet. She made the class a lot easier. You only really need to study the pretests. She gives so many hints in class about the exams which is very helpful. No surprises on exams. The class itself is very content heavy which can be a bit overwhelming at times but she does her best to tell you exactly whats on the exam.
Elle est vraiment gentille. Elle est la Meilleure des prof que j'ai jamais eu. Elle est vraiment. Tres patiente et se soucie de la reussite reussite de ses etudiants.

Francoise isn't a native english speaker, so she has a thick accent, but she's really nice & caring. You're only tested on the ppts. Some figures from the textbook aren't on the slides, but they are on her ppt, so make sure you come to class as they're testable. Overall Interesting course content with a caring prof is always a solid combo.

Loved this class! Francoise made it super easy to get a good grade because she had lots of quizzes + assignments that were easy As. She also gave pretests for the midterm and final that were almost exactly the same as those on the real tests. She's also a very sweet lady who you can tell actually cares about her students.

Honestly, the sweetest prof in the world. I have never had a prof that genuinely wants students to succeed in her class. Study her pretests for all her quizzes to get easy As, the midterm is a little tricky so study ahead of time . 2 group assignments that are freebees (free 100s) Her accent can be a little hard to understand but shes so nice!
Take this course with her. You will thank me later. Her accent is thick, but she really cares for her students and tries to simplify things as much as possible for success.

She was an excellent professor that taught all the information very thoroughly! She tells you exactly what to expect for her tests and gives many opportunities for boosting your grade (midterms, tests, assignments). However she is very french and this slowed her teaching by a lot. We had to skim over some of the class material.

All around amazing teacher. Is very clear on what will be on the exams. Gives pre-tests and takes questions from those to put on exams. Nothing is a surprise. Gives all the information needed in slides. Only thing is she will give images to see in book in class. But will also be in the corrigé of pre-tests. Easy A+

A very nice lady who cares about the students and loves what she does. She is very bubbly and energetic. This is only a make-up course so the grades don't fully matter. Study the slides and your notes and everything will make sense. Good preparation of you're going to take BIO or ANP.

She really can't explain things well in English, but she tries her best. Do the work, pay attention in class, and you'll do really well. Also, do the textbook questions- most are multiple choice with the answers in the back, and she puts them word for word as bonus marks on the exam!
teacherRatingTags: ['EXTRA CREDIT', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: shes very nice, but  all over the place.  will mention not to study certain content for exams but change her mind and put it on the midterms. very hard to understand (accent) and likes to use chalk board drawings which are unreadable.  her exams poorly written (she can't write in proper English). Got 92% on first midterm only to fail the 2nd.

Very quiet and her accent makes it very hard to listen and understand her lectures. Takes longer to mark tests. Tells you what to and not to study, but puts stuff from the not to study. Will give her credit, she gives you a few extra questions on exams to help marks a bit, but I would not recommend her.
Les classes magistraux sont vraiment longue ! Mais elle donne beaucoup d'information sur les examens... Énormément de par-coeur !!

She's very nice but there's no feedback on exams, she doesn't always show up to office hours, and you can't understand what she's saying because she talks so quietly. She's very passionate about the subject though, and tells you exactly what's on the exam so you can do extremely well if you try hard. Overall very nice woman, average teacher.

I'm not impressed. I needed to ask her something about the assignment that we bring to the exam to use as an open book thing, so I emailed her almost 2 weeks ago, still no response. I came to her scheduled office hours, no one is here. She's impossible to reach and she's very slow at getting back tests. She seems really nice, but awful teacher.

I never liked bio but needed this class for my program, so granted I did go in with a bad attitude towards it. She is very quiet and hard to understand. Her mid term questions are out of nowhere. She mentions stuff to study and everything but those will be on the exam. She is very sweet and nice but all over the place with her thoughts.

Dedicated to biology, speaks quietly so make sure to ask her to use the mic early on in semester. Good, thorough diagrams. Makes sure students understand before moving on. Gives Midterm & final hints. Need textbook for independent assignment (part of final).

If you're good at learning from the textbook, this course isn't bad. Sometimes her accent is hard to understand. I often doze off in her lectures. She's nice and ready to help but I found I mostly learned from the textbook.
Explained things on chalkboard very clearly. Not just boring ppt.  Allowed to choose some questions to answer on exams
Explained things on chalkboard very clearly. Not just boring ppt.  Allowed to choose some questions to answer on exams
Explained things on chalkboard very clearly. Not just boring ppt.  Allowed to choose some questions to answer on exams
Explained things on chalkboard very clearly. Not just boring ppt.

Atroce. Elle semble stressée et elle explique mal. Le manuel est en anglais et est accompagné d'un immense document de questions qu'elle a composé, donc on fait un travail de traduction en préparation à l'examen (on a droit au document à l'examen par contre). N'allez pas au cours, ça ne fait que vous exaspérer. À prendre seulement en cas de besoin.

Prof très gentille, examen le plus facile concernant l'anatomie du corps. Il fallait faire 40 des 46 choix multiples en plus de d'autres figures au choix. Examen de rêve, prenez ce cours. Cependant, prof parle trop vite et le cours est plate des fois. En général, ce cours est bon pour prendre une science assez facile.

Prof est très gentille, ses diapos sont très complètes, reflètent bien la matière à l'examen.  Ses notes de cours sont un peu moins bien organisées.  Mais aucun souci, examen style: Répondez 45 des 65 QCM et Répondez à SEULEMENT 1 des 3 questions réponses courtes. :):):)  Examens de rêve.  Sérieusement.

Classe très facile. Elle vous dit pratiquement ce qui est sur l'examen. Elle est disponible pour vous aider. Le livre n'est pas vraiment utile, vous avez qu'à lire ses power point, faire les questions pratique et étudier les diagrammes et vous aurez une très bonne note. Je sais vraiment pas comment quelqu'un peu mal faire dans ce cours...

The worst prof I've had. Course based on an English book (the practice is defensible ONLY when there are no French textbooks), and an out-of-print edition on top of that! Refused to clarify some areas, saying they wouldn't be on exam, then put them on there. Doesn't know her stuff either; in every topic I know something about, she made mistakes
She is well organized and the exams are exactly what was seen in class.  Read the powerpoints and do the questions in the pack and you should be good to go.

tres organisee, si vous participez elle va vous adorer par contre ses questions d'examens sont...hmmm....out of nowhere...apprenez les photos meme si elle vous avise du contraire..surtout zoomastigophore

Her exams questions came out of nowhere, she was constantly confused and never remembered anything she had told us. Everyone did more poorly than they thought because we had no idea what was expected. 3rd year Kinetics students were doing poorly
